      },
      "date": "2012-09-14 08:50:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)\n\nChris or Li Wei, can you comment whether setting USE_OFD in local.sh will work on autotest today?  I think there is a separate bug open to have the autotest config source local.sh for these kinds of parameters/defaults, but I don't think it has happened yet?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "f87a524e519425719affaf744cf6cba188908706",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-09-14 20:20:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/68026194-fea4-11e1-a707-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "baa38c2620e237a090b258e59dd98a43776eb413",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-17 06:57:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nAndreas actually brought up this idea quite some time ago.  I didn't implement it because the correct way would be introducing an initialization phase in Test Framework that happens after loading a configuration file like local.sh, ncli.sh, etc..  Then, this check could be done easily in that phase without the potential of breaking Autotest.  The work was too much at that time.\n\nSince users shall not have to deal with USE_OFD and OSTFSTYPE, I tend to think putting this check into local.sh is not necessary; developers and Autotest will learn to not use osd-zfs with obdfilter.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "6d75366005ac47e95983e4666b38341fc7136f86",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 198,
        "name": "Minh Diep",
        "email": "mdiep@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "mdiep"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-18 15:26:46.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 3.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "b2489a118073cd71556bca937e458bca535ec6cb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-18 15:34:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e71ab853591a5eb55bfeb182136c5219798980b5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-18 15:41:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nSorry, but this is still not completely correct.  You may have to check on a per-node basis---whether an OSS needs to host ZFS-based OSTs.  (See node_fstypes().)  IMHO, if one requires ZFS OSTs but requests OBDFilter, then let things fail, since this is not part of normal Lustre usage but only testing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d33b599017c42ed825414bd9722ab622c33534e3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-18 15:44:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAnother concern is that changing USE_OFD at load_module time could be surprising.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "eeab9a11d3065a260fffb9837b41dabc1ec915a0",
      "author": {
