    {
      "id": "a88bdb78f12866ffbbac9038d7c4e279f2ba53e9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-20 23:10:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLi Wei,\nThe need for USE_OFD is only temporary for 2.3 and master, but will be obsolete by the time 2.4 is released, since ofd will have replaced obdfilter entirely. I don't think it is worthwhile to make matters overly complex in the meantime, given its short expected lifespan.\n\nThe goal is to allow ZFS to work in the test environment during this time of transition, and for developers running testing locally. As such, I'd prefer not to block this patch longer if there are not defects that would cause problems during normal usage.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "4e9ac052e038101ce8a4cc5b853eab72eeeb29d3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-21 08:50:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nSorry if I misunderstand the situation, but won't existing code work if Autotest specify USE_OFD=yes when testing with ZFS OSTs?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "4084b39a2b1e8047fd8f058e9d1bea86b795e98d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 198,
        "name": "Minh Diep",
        "email": "mdiep@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "mdiep"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-21 16:00:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nI don't think autotest will specify US_OFD=yes when user use OSTFSTYPE=zfs. That's the point of this patch trying to fix. we must force OFD when test zfs. otherwise, setup will fail",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "525e954b483be841f0d917ae3aab253a007675c0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-23 01:24:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nThe original idea is that users?either Autotest, developers, or external testers?shall specify USE_OFD to test the non-default OSS stack in 2.3 or pre-release 2.4.  Asking Autotest to specify \"USE_OFD\" and \"LOAD_MODULES_REMOTE\" is a natural and straightforward solution, no?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "af96292f31dbf5cfcf8dbcf5654347fc98ea6fad",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 198,
        "name": "Minh Diep",
        "email": "mdiep@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "mdiep"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-24 15:52:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nAutotest does not use local.sh directly. Perhaps what you suggest should be in another ticket.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c4d06b0f12dc4121df1fb0c417a730e7d8027f7c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 01:49:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c65f384459234c97118bd8d3fc9b397ae376b780",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 06:10:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLi Wei, I think the main reason not to involve autotest to set this environment variable is that this is not something that we developers can do directly, unlike patches to the test framework. It was my hipe that this oatch could be landed relatively quickly so that more people testing ZFS will not need to understand so many details of the testing system to do so. \n\nSecondly, the need for USE_OFD is limited to specific Lustre versions, so adding it to autotest for every version is added co plenitude that isn't needed for most releases, while putting it into Lustre itself can be done for the specific releases where it is needed, then removed again when obdfilter is removed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9b4a5c5e47a427d7dc20e06fe0d2d980abf18ed5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 07:29:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: No score\n\nAndreas, the facet_fstype() call is incorrect and introduces a different name for what we have been using (\"OST_FSTYPE\" verse \"OSTFSTYPE\").  Changing USE_OFD in load_modules() is also not straightforward.  Well, I can't give it \"+1\", but I have removed the \"-1\", so that your \"+2\" vote shall let this patch pass.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9efd56ad6dbc5d33ea0d16c566a1176ee9e32288",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 12:13:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nLi Wei, I agree that the incorrect use of facet_fstype() is something that should be fixed before landing the patch.  Mu understanding is that changing this to $(facet_fstype ost1) should be the correct usage?\n\nWhat I'm trying to avoid is an increasingly complex solution to a relatively simple problem (that specifying \"OSTFSTYPE=zfs\" should \"just work\" for whomever uses it).\n\nIf there is an equally simple solution that you think is more correct, I'd be happy to see it, but I don't think the short-term lifespan of this workaround is worthy of investing a huge amount of time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
